24/05/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan again called on the United States and anti-terror coalition allies Wednesday (May 23rd) to demonstrate concrete results in the fight against the Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK). 
Appearing on TV after the deadly bomb blast in Ankara, Erdogan stressed that Turkey, the United States and Iraq should resolve the problem together. 
He also again hinted that a cross-border operation by the Turkish Army in northern Iraq remains an option, to protect peace in Turkey. 
(Milliyet, Radikal - 24/05/07; TurkishPress.com - 23/05/07)
